[recv] {"type": "message_end", "message": {"role": "assistant", "content": [{"type": "thinking", "thinking": "**Considering futures and channels**\n\nI'm thinking about how to add a listener to complete a future that invokes a listener on an event loop. I'm considering using an executor for scheduling channel closures. It's important to run pending tasks and assert that the channel isn't open. I might also need to handle errors carefully since using onError will also close the channel. Additionally, I want to test cancellation during channel inactivity, and I'm curious about a potential native-image. Time to focus on coding and using Assertions AssertJ!\n\n**Reviewing channel utility**\n\nI'm trying to focus on keeping the package consistent while using utility classes. I want to avoid deprecated APIs, so I need to check if EmbeddedChannel and channel.finishAndReleaseAll are still valid. I'll use try-finally for caution with EventLoop tasks. EmbeddedChannel.runPendingTasks is public, but I think I can skip runScheduledPendingTasks since sleeps aren't necessary. When constructing the channel, I need to add the handler correctly and ensure it registers properly in the event loop.", "thinkingSignature": "{\"id\":\"rs_0156de0e717a13000169f69b1b43cc8195b6a44f1156127a8f\",\"type\":\"reasoning\",\"encrypted_content\":\"gAAAAABp9psuiuO1uNtrnZtQ7PQUvSow7PWdTXp_qwdu96Syv_2vQCv5fo11cAD3c_BGm1Hj24TiK_RsYpo1O1RtzUvwAdmq0P9pXcnn-ZjVblv7knJ0Tf03f1dD8xj0Z7yfI27On0VJAC-IOQpsOwPFYIGlxYdmAXxCXmrJOmXTuadTh6CWxB_080wgoOGi11Vc734dwvcbzHbwM-K5-4-RSE-RWt_aWJ9BzyZWwNQ8yYVHmYMKjO7qSthf0Y6_d9tYR_poVVaaWRrkMdsBwd-lzON8zs0BbYQCz4fBXH7adS139OPGj4mOblzg_xWTYqf2GJLM_dyd8LjHLGD7VAMKvvMOt7lsmUAY0t2tLWVmOic2unPltp2noEcjPTP3IFSbjPbLHdAVsSMzjjbX-ETLMpoSzmuMGMCJgWSkUqgHOE9pSwrEyIYFLRbbYWE-3kzmfbTHTPW38T6WDBYs_LKQNli0IUl6h1g2rdYGtg2FCumCIVXdgPFStLU2p5WjpzDghp3tZm_M1Gd5TfxK5LFwqh3w3tg5_rt9hPG1gufvNuFw17pFsJq_vvhXUaPF5IFR7MTNEeAfbt3p4GXqt_aSje2nsyksK-U8cC9LTO66B4UfdvPC20zMOi4xz5hF2-KOKSXLTCjeCO-XZv3DoTMjWY